<TITLE> At least 10 killed in road accidents </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 20 (bdnews24.com)  At least 10 people died and dozens sustained injuries in road accidents across the country on Saturday, local police officials said. CHITTAGONG Four people died at Sitakunda in Chittagong as a bus ran into a CNG-run autorickshaw on the Dhaka-Chittagong highway at around noon. Sitakunda highway police chief Wahid Siddiqui told bdnews24.com that all four passengers of the autorickshaw were killed. Mohammad Selim, 27, and Nila Chakrabarty, 31, died on the spot. The other two, Lakkhan Das, 30, and an unidentified man, were critically injured and taken to Chittagong Medical College Hospital where they died. SYLHET Three people were killed and 20 others were injured in separate road accidents in Sylhet. Osmaninagar police chief Nur Alam said pedestrians Mohammad Khalilur Rahman, 35, and Rahmat Ullah, 55, died as the driver of a truck lost control of it and ran over them. Abu Sayeed, a sub-inspector at Sylhet highway, said a CNG-run auto-rickshaw driver died on the spot and 20 other passengers sustained injuries as a bus hit the auto-rickshaw on the Sylhet-Dhaka highway at 3:30pm. COX'S BAZAR A micro-bus driver and a helper died and 12 passengers sustained injuries on Saturday morning as it collided with a truck head-on in Cox's Bazar. Ramu police chief Mohammad Shahjahan said bus driver Mohammad Morshed, 40, died on the scene while helper Mohammad Abul Kalam Azad succumbed to injuries at Cox's Bazar Sadar Hospital. JESSORE A police constable died and four others were injured in a road accident in Jessore between a police patrol car and a pick-up truck of suspected cattle thieves Saturday morning. Abhaynagar police chief Abu Bakkar said Naopara highway police were chasing after the pick-up and at one stage tried to overtake it, when the pick-up hit the patrol car, which plunged into a ditch. The pick-up managed to flee. Bakkar said constable Yunus died on the spot while Shahabul, 48, Fazlur, 48, Ruhul Amin, 42, driver Sunil sustained injuries and were taken to Khulna Medical College. bdne
